<!--Knowledge Inspiration: Pug Templare Engine :: FreeCode Camp 
***** To Set-Up Pug Template Engine *****
1. Create Root Folder
2. Create html folder
3. in html folder, create 'index.pug' file
4. At top of index.pug file, type 'doctype html'
5. in vs code terminal, type 'pug -w ./ -o .index.html -P'
6, Begin coding in index.pug
--> 

Code Example:
html
  head
  body 
  header#header 
    h1#pageTitle  Hello World
    p. 
      This is the world
      as we know it.
    ul 
      li.bullets Item 1
      li.bullets item 2
      li.bullets item 3
    
    input(type="password" name="inpPwd" data-js=`${1>= 2 ? "OK" : "Not Ok"}`)